{"id":691604,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oiva_Toikka","text":"Oiva Kalervo Toikka (29 May 1931 \u2013 22 April 2019) was a Finnish glass designer. He designed for Iittala. He was best known for his bird designs for Iittala. He trained in ceramics at the University of Art and Design in Helsinki. He also worked as a stage and costume designer. He designed textiles for Marimekko.\nToikka was born in Viipuri. He died on 22 April 2019, at the age of 87.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Finnish_people","surface_form":"Finnish","offset":56},{"uri":"Glass","surface_form":"glass","offset":64},{"uri":"Designer","surface_form":"designer","offset":70},{"uri":"Iittala","surface_form":"Iittala","offset":96},{"uri":"Bird","surface_form":"bird","offset":131},{"uri":"Ceramic","surface_form":"ceramic","offset":171},{"uri":"Aalto_University_School_of_Arts%2C_Design_and_Architecture","surface_form":"University of Art and Design","offset":187},{"uri":"Helsinki","surface_form":"Helsinki","offset":219},{"uri":"Stage","surface_form":"stage","offset":249},{"uri":"Costume","surface_form":"costume","offset":259},{"uri":"Textile","surface_form":"textile","offset":289},{"uri":"Marimekko","surface_form":"Marimekko","offset":302},{"uri":"Vyborg","surface_form":"Viipuri","offset":332}]}